SAN FRANCISCO (SFO), UAL1871, B738. UAL1871 was pushed onto the ramp from Gate D16. The pilot reported to ground control that they may have pushed into another aircraft. Airfield ops and the fire department were called to the scene and confirmed that they had pushed back into an aircraft in Gate E5, UAL769, which was proposed to depart but had not yet pushed from the gate. No injuries were reported; however, the aircraft were pulled back into the gate, and both aircraft deboarded. It was reported to the tower from airfield ops that UAL1871 had a bent horizontal stabilizer and that UAL769 had damaged the exhaust column. FAA Form 8020-9 was received. POB: Unknown, Injuries: None, Damage: Substantial. 9/2/2025 0412Z.
